Johannesburg- Pro Kid’s younger brother, DJ Citi Lyts has been murdered. Citi Lyts, real named Sandile Mkhize, was shot and killed in an armed robbery at his Soweto joint in Vilakazi street. According to a source close to Citi Lyts’  family, the artist was closing his joint at about 10 pm last night when a group of armed thugs pounced on him and fatally shot him and fled after robbing him of his cash. Gauteng Police Spokesperson Mavela Masondo said the police were still waiting for the details of the incident. His father, Zwelakhe Mkhize, said he was unable to comment as he did not have the details. The rapper, Pro Kid, real name, Linda Mkhize died in 2018 after suffering hemosuccus pancreatitis – which is a rare cause of gastrointestinal bleeding.  SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here. 